medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Symptoms began 18 months ago. The patient reported accompanying dysmenorrhea and dyspareunia. Initial diagnostic workup included elevated prolactin levels, with inconclusive pelvic and transvaginal ultrasounds. A hysteroscopy revealed multiple septa in the reproductive tract. Following failed attempts to conceive naturally, the patient underwent two trials of ovulation induction leading to pregnancy.
medical_history.past_medical_history: History of hypothyroidism, well controlled by treatment. No other significant past medical or surgical history.
medical_history.family_history: Family history was negative for any known anomaly.
